	From ejnorman%dogie@unix2.macc.wisc.edu Tue Apr 12 18:15:51 1988

	I still don't see what's wrong with just setting up a nickname
	domain

	[ four "good" reasons why he should do this ]

1) It propagates "wrong" information (you said it avoids the `it worked
   last week syndrome') -- the post office will only forward your
   mail for a small amount of time.  I think we've waited 3 years
   for "seismo" (unqualified) to go away, even though they moved
   long ago ...

2) It's an administrative nightmare.  I know I wouldn't want thousands
   of users saying to me "please alias mit-ai for me" ...

I think the solution of $HOSTALIASES is sufficient.

/jordan

